14/01/2008
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The leader of the Serb List (SL) political alliance, Andrija Mandic, announced on Sunday (January 13th) he plans to run for president in this year's elections.
They will take place after incumbent Filip Vujanovic's term ends on May 22nd, and will be the first presidential vote since the country became independent.
Mandic, whose party is the biggest opposition force in Montenegro, told SL supporters that he decided to run because his party has the best vision and enjoys increasing public support.
(Vijesti - 14/01/08;
MINA - 13/01/08)
